19:00.917 --> 19:03.709
I tell "My mama's
so dumb" jokes.

19:03.750 --> 19:07.709
I love it. Francine,
take the pain and throw it
right at Stan. Do it!

19:07.750 --> 19:12.125
Stan, you have
the undeserved ego
of Jeremy Piven,

19:12.166 --> 19:15.333
the annoying
self-righteousness
of Sean Penn...

19:15.375 --> 19:18.792
and the unbearable hypocrisy
of Rush Limbaugh.

19:18.834 --> 19:23.583
What I'm trying to say
is you're almost as bad
a person as Rachael Ray.

19:38.834 --> 19:41.250
Why are you laughing?
That wasn't funny.

19:41.291 --> 19:43.667
That's like the meanest thing
anyone's ever said to anyone.

19:43.709 --> 19:46.291
What the hell's going on here?
Where's the hurt feelings?

19:46.333 --> 19:49.875
Roger, we can say
these things to each other
because we're family.

19:49.917 --> 19:52.542
It doesn't hurt my feelings,
because I still know
they love me.

19:52.583 --> 19:54.458
Well, your roast
hurt my feelings.

19:54.500 --> 19:56.458
Wait a minute.

19:56.500 --> 19:59.291
You don't consider yourself
part of this family, do you?

19:59.333 --> 20:02.166
No. 'Cause I'm not.
Are you kidding me?

20:02.208 --> 20:05.709
We tried to throw you
a bowling party.
We did the roast you wanted.

20:05.750 --> 20:09.542
If after all this time,
you still don't feel part of
this family, it's your hang-up.

20:09.583 --> 20:12.458
Roger, we love you.
You're a Smith.

20:12.500 --> 20:14.667
If you can't accept that,
go-- yourself.

20:14.709 --> 20:18.041
Oh, my God.

20:18.083 --> 20:20.792
I am a part
of this family.

20:20.834 --> 20:24.333
You do love me.
I feel it now.

20:24.375 --> 20:28.166
I'm-- I'm letting it
wash over me.

20:28.208 --> 20:32.583
Look at me.
I'm crying like Francine when
she watches Grey's Anatomy.

20:32.625 --> 20:35.792
I just feel so sorry
for those poor actors.

20:35.834 --> 20:38.500
Hey, Roger.

20:38.542 --> 20:40.875
Go take some Euphoria
and rape the data journal.

